%C A128179 General case see A211161. Let B and C be sequences. By b(n) and c(n) denote elements B and C respectively. Table T(n,k) = b(n), if k is odd, c(k) if k is even read by antidiagonals. For this sequence b(n)=n, b(n)=A000027(n), c(n)=0, c(n)=A000004(n). - _Boris Putievskiy_, Feb 05 2013
%H A128179 Boris Putievskiy, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1212.2732">Transformations [of] Integer Sequences And Pairing Functions</a> arXiv:1212.2732 [math.CO], 2012.
%F A128179 A097807 * A002260 as infinite lower triangular matrices. k-th column = (k, 0, k, 0, ...).
%F A128179 From _Boris Putievskiy_, Feb 05 2013: (Start)
%F A128179 T(n,k) = (1-(-1)^k)*n/2;
%F A128179 a(n) = (1-(-1)^A004736(n))*A002260(n)/2;
%F A128179 a(n) = (1-(-1)^j)*i/2, where i = n-t*(t+1)/2, j = (t*t+3*t+4)/2-n, t = floor((-1+sqrt(8*n-7))/2). (End)
